_comment: Human corrections to LLM judgment errors. Applied during GT computation at the aggregated judgment level.

G1_allergy.reason: Review is POSITIVE - customer praised allergy handling ('took my unusual anaphylaxis case seriously'), no reaction occurred
Review mentions 'allergic reaction' but no actual symptoms described - failed accommodation without ingestion per Option A (strict) interpretation

Review is about BEDBUG BITES at a hotel, not food allergy. Reviewer explicitly ruled out allergy: "initially thought it was an allergic reaction... Then I found that there was a small bite in the center... realized these are bedbug bites"
No allergy mentioned. Reviewer describes "bad reaction to the food" causing missed work day - this is food poisoning/food quality issue, not allergic reaction
Vegetarian dietary preference, not allergy. Reviewer was served chicken soup and nearly vomited - this is ethical/preference aversion, no allergic condition mentioned
No allergy mentioned. Reviewer describes food poisoning symptoms ("the runs and throwing up") after eating corn dogs - classic food poisoning, not allergic reaction
No allergy mentioned. "Felt punky for about 12 hours" after eating bad soup - food quality/poisoning issue. No allergen or allergy condition described
No allergy mentioned. "Made me sick. Don't know why. Food just tasted off to me. Maybe it was me." - vague food quality issue, no allergy mentioned
Per definition: no visible symptoms (hives/swelling) or medication mentioned. 'Super sick' and 'sick all night' without these specific indicators = mild, not moderate.

G1_dietary.reason: Food poisoning from contaminated food (cleaning solution taste), no dietary restriction mentioned. This is a food safety issue, not dietary accommodation failure.
Duplicate of c8EmPXynkT3hP1D3nEhoQw - same food poisoning incident, no dietary restriction involved.
BURN INJURY from hot soup spill due to unsecured lid - not a dietary incident. Physical injury from hot liquid, unrelated to dietary restrictions.
Salmonella food poisoning requiring hospitalization - no dietary restriction mentioned. Pure food safety issue.
Bug in soup causing food poisoning concern - no dietary restriction mentioned. Food safety/hygiene issue, not dietary accommodation.
Food poisoning (vomiting) with cockroaches observed - no dietary restriction mentioned. Food safety issue, not dietary accommodation.

Diabetic reviewer's blood sugar spiked after eating French toast and needed insulin. This is expected diabetic response to high-sugar food, not a restaurant accommodation failure. No reasonable expectation for restaurants to label glycemic index.
Food poisoning (violent illness) from sampler plate - no dietary restriction mentioned. Reported to health department as food safety issue.
FALSE POSITIVE - This is a 5-STAR POSITIVE REVIEW! "die with first bite" is hyperbolic praise meaning the food is delicious, not an actual incident.
No dietary restriction. Reviewer discovered they cannot digest raw fish - personal tolerance discovery, not accommodation failure.
No dietary restriction. Food quality complaint (nausea from bad food), not dietary accommodation issue.
5-STAR POSITIVE REVIEW. "Last time I tried a new sushi place I ended up desperately sick" refers to DIFFERENT restaurant. This review praises KitzMo.
No dietary restriction. Food poisoning warning about "outdated seafood" - food safety issue, not dietary.
JOKE REVIEW. "salt shaker fell out my buttocks" is obvious humor. Salty salad complaint, no dietary restriction.
